        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued July 13 at 8:09AM CDT until July 13 at 11:00AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>FFWSJT

The National Weather Service in San Angelo has issued a

* Flash Flood Warning for...
West Central Menard County in west central Texas...

* Until 1100 AM CDT.

* At 804 AM CDT, Emergency Management reported the low water
crossing at the San Saba River near Fort McKavett under water on
FM 864. Between 2 and 5 inches of rain have fallen on the
headwaters of the San Saba River. The expected rainfall rate is
0.25 to 0.5 inches in 1 hour. Additional rainfall amounts of 0.25
to 0.5 inches are possible in the warned area. Flash flooding is
already occurring.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms
producing flash flooding.

SOURCE...Emergency management reported.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams,
urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses.

* Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Menard, Fort Mckavett and Camp Sol Mayer.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
